---

  Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat

oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into ¼-inch-thick pieces.

Roughly chop @parsley{¼%ounce}. Quarter @gouda cheese{2%slice}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @ketchup{1%unit}, @apricot jam{1%unit}, and

@sriracha{1%teaspoon}; set glaze aside.

== Garlic Herb Potatoes & Carrots ==

In a #large microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4

servings), @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and

@pepper{pinch}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until butter has

melted, ~{30-45%seconds}. Remove plastic wrap and stir until thoroughly

combined.

Add potatoes, carrots, and parsley to bowl with butter mixture. Toss until

thoroughly combined. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Transfer veggies to one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} (for 4, spread

veggies out across entire sheet). Roast on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (you'll add

more to the sheet in Step 4). Wash out bowl.

== Meatloaves ==

In bowl used for veggies, soak @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup} with

@pork ramen stock concentrate{1%unit} and 1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4

servings); stir until pasty. Add @ground pork{10%ounce}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon},

@salt{½%tsp} (1 tsp for 4), and @pepper{pinch}; mix to combine.

Form pork mixture into two ½-inch-thick rounds (four rounds for 4). Dividing

evenly, place gouda in the center of each round. Gently fold meat around

cheese, shaping and sealing to create 1-inch-tall loaves.

== Assembly and Roasting ==

Once veggies have roasted 5 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully place

meatloaves, seam sides down, on opposite side of sheet. (For 4 servings, leave

veggies roasting; arrange meatloaves on a second lightly oiled baking sheet.)

Transfer half the glaze to a second small bowl and reserve (you'll use it in

the next step). Brush meatloaves with remaining glaze. Roast on top rack for

~{13%minutes}. (For 4, roast meatloaves on middle rack.)

Remove sheet with meatloaves from oven and carefully brush meatloaves with

reserved glaze.

Return to oven and roast until meatloaves are cooked through, veggies are tender,

and glaze is tacky, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Divide veggies and meatloaves between plates and serve.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.